      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Josef Goradza (1933-2008) was a German-American photographer and later Ramakrishna monk.  Born 
		in Silesia, Germany, Goradza came to the United States in 1953.  He became an American citizen and 
		served in the U.S. Army during the Korean War.  In 1973 he joined the Ramakrishna-Vivekananda Center of 
		New York as a monastic member, taking the name Brahmachari Sadashiva Chaitanya.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Josef Goradza Collection</emph> consists of several hundred black and white photographs.  Many are 
			of individuals, of New York street scenes or of nature (flowers, leaves, etc.).  Unfortunately none of the photographs are identified.</p><p>The collection also includes contact sheets, photographs of 
			the work of artists Ezio Martinelli and some personal photographs, with a few negatives and color transparencies.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
